Malignant fibrous histiocytoma in a recurrent thoracic chordoma: case report and literature review.
 Malignant transformation in a recurrent chordoma in the thoracic region is extremely uncommon.
 One new case, as well as a review of spinal chordomas that have undergone malignant transformation, is reported.
 Such cases emphasize the importance of the aggressive initial surgical treatment of spinal tumors.
